headline.main: CELEBES IS SHELLED BY TOKYO WASHIPS; Town of Menado on Dutch Isle South of Philippines Struck -- Little Damage Done PLANES ALSO IN ATTACKS Netherlands Indies Leaders Want Allies to Coordinate Fight in Those Possessions

lead_paragraph: BATAVIA, Netherlands Indies, Dec. 31 (UP) -- Japanese destroyers shelled Menado, a town of 28,000 population near the northern tip of the Netherland island of Celebes, without causing serious damage or casualties, but Japanese planes killed three persons in raids on "various small places in the outer provinces," it was announced here today.
abstract: Jap planes raid N I outer provs
